Remco for Touristic Villages in Talks to Sell 3 Hotels, Mal Says

-- B y   O l a   G a l a l
-- 
2011-06-06T05:47:34Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-06-06/remco-for-touristic-villages-in-talks-to-sell-3-hotels-mal-says.html
Remco for Touristic Villages, an
Egyptian builder of resorts, is in talks to sell three hotels in
Hurgada and Sharm El Sheikh with a likely value of 1.55 billion
Egyptian pounds ($261 million),  Al Mal  reported, citing Vice
Chairman Onsi Youssef.  The company, which is due to meet with foreign investors on
June 15 to decide which hotels to put up for sale, needs cash to
pay dividends and increase its ability to execute projects, the
newspaper cited Youssef as saying.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Ola Galal in Cairo at 
 ogalal@bloomberg.net .  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
 Stephen Voss  at 
 sev@bloomberg.net . 